oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Developments in the Dairy Industry for the 70's
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Knox, W. D.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: If it is possible to have a heartwarming experience on a cold winter morning in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, this is such an occasion for me. First, we were personally and professionally delighted five years ago with the formation of the American Association of Bovine Practitioners. The vision and the statesmanship of your leadership at that time has resulted in immeasurable benefits to the dairy industry. Since our life, too, is committed to the welfare of those who own and tend the foster mothers of the human race, we welcome every increase in professional advancement which makes the dairy cow more efficient because of her improved health and regular reproduction.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1972; 31-34
